CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773360185
OL,3,CWitness denies 'planning alibi,'
OL,4,CNatalie McNally murder trial told
OL,6,FHer partner, Stephen McCullagh, 36, of
OL,7,FWoodland Gardens in Lisburn, is on
OL,8,Ftrial for her murder.
OL,10,FHe has denied the charge.
OL,12,FHe has instead pointed the finger of
OL,13,Fblame at a former boyfriend of hers.
OL,15,FMs McNally's ex-partner gave evidence
OL,16,Fat the trial earlier this week and
OL,17,Fflatly rejected suggestions he was
OL,18,Finvolved in her murder.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773360185
OL,3,CWitness denies 'planning alibi,'
OL,4,CNatalie McNally murder trial told
OL,6,FCalled to give evidence was the ex-
OL,7,Fpartner's now ex-girlfriend who was
OL,8,Fliving with him in his flat in
OL,9,FDecember 2022.
OL,11,FShe spend a second day being cross-
OL,12,Fexamined by defence barrister John
OL,13,FKearney KC who asked her about
OL,14,Fstatements she made to the PSNI.
OL,16,FThe woman told police that on the
OL,17,Fnight Ms McNally was murdered, she and
OL,18,Fher partner had spend the evening
OL,19,Ftogether in his flat and that he fell
OL,20,Fasleep watching the World Cup Final on
OL,21,FTV.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773360185
OL,3,CWitness denies 'planning alibi,'
OL,4,CNatalie McNally murder trial told
OL,6,FShe also told police she went to bed
OL,7,Fand that he followed her into the
OL,8,Fbedroom at some point later.
OL,10,FWhen asked why she didn't tell the
OL,11,Fpolice about watching a Harry Potter
OL,12,Ffilm after the football or getting up
OL,13,Fin the middle of the night to go to
OL,14,Fthe toilet in a statement made on
OL,15,FDecember 20, 2022, she replied: "I
OL,16,Freally didn't go into that much detail
OL,17,Fbecause I didn't understand what was
OL,18,Fgoing on.
OL,20,F"I didn't even know someone was dead
OL,21,Fat this point."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773360185
OL,3,CWitness denies 'planning alibi,'
OL,4,CNatalie McNally murder trial told
OL,6,FMr Kearney also questioned the woman
OL,7,Fabout a second statement she made to
OL,8,Fpolice two days later and
OL,9,F"differences" in the two.
OL,11,FThe witness said the second statement
OL,12,Fto police was made "in the middle of
OL,13,Fthe night" and just after her partner
OL,14,Fhad been arrested on suspicion on
OL,15,Fmurdering Ms McNally.
OL,17,FShe said she was "not in a good state
OL,18,Fat this point" and her memory "wasn't
OL,19,Fgreat."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773360185
OL,3,CWitness denies 'planning alibi,'
OL,4,CNatalie McNally murder trial told
OL,6,FAsked if she and her partner had
OL,7,Fdiscussed the Sunday evening and had
OL,8,F"sat down and compared notes" prior to
OL,9,Fhis arrest, she replied: "No.
OL,11,F"I knew he had not done this, so in my
OL,12,Fbrain I did not think there was any
OL,13,Fchance of him coming and getting
OL,14,Farrested.
OL,16,F"He asked me 'do you think they are
OL,17,Faccusing me of doing this?' and I said
OL,18,F'no, don't be ridiculous, you didn't
OL,19,Fdo this, there's no chance of you
OL,20,Fgetting arrested' so I was very much
OL,21,Fin shock when he was arrested.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773360185
OL,3,CWitness denies 'planning alibi,'
OL,4,CNatalie McNally murder trial told
OL,6,F"There was no talk of what went on
OL,7,Fthat night between us. I did not think
OL,8,Fhe was going to get arrested.
OL,10,F"We did not sit there and plan out any
OL,11,Fsort of alibi."
OL,13,FThe witness also confirmed she told
OL,14,Fpolice she had deleted Ms McNally's
OL,15,Fnumber from her partner's home.
OL,17,FWhen asked why she had done this, the
OL,18,Fwitness said "I didn't want him
OL,19,Ftalking to other women."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773360185
OL,3,CWitness denies 'planning alibi,'
OL,4,CNatalie McNally murder trial told
OL,6,FShe said she was initially told Ms
OL,7,FMcNally was a "platonic friend who he
OL,8,Fhad lived with in the past, like a
OL,9,Fflatmate-type situation" but that over
OL,10,Ftime she felt "there was a bit more to
OL,11,Fthe relationship than he originally
OL,12,Ftold me."
OL,14,FThe witness also confirmed that on the
OL,15,Fevening of Sunday December 18, 2022,
OL,16,Fwhile her boyfriend slept on the sofa
OL,17,Fshe checked his phone and found "a
OL,18,Fvery small amount" of messages between
OL,19,Fhim and Ms McNally.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773360185
OL,3,CWitness denies 'planning alibi,'
OL,4,CNatalie McNally murder trial told
OL,6,FShe said she never saw any messages
OL,7,Fbetween the two "of a sexual nature"
OL,8,Fbut felt there was more to their
OL,9,Frelationship than she had been told.
OL,11,FThe witness was then shown a document
OL,12,Fwhich detailed a series of messages
OL,13,Fbetween her now-ex partner and Ms
OL,14,FMcNally which were exchanged on
OL,15,FDecember 18, 2022 and were retained on
OL,16,FMs McNally's phone.
OL,18,FMr Kearney asked if those were the
OL,19,Fmessages she saw and the witness said
OL,20,Fher partner deleted messages "so I may
OL,21,Fnot have seen all of this."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773360185
OL,3,CWitness denies 'planning alibi,'
OL,4,CNatalie McNally murder trial told
OL,6,FMr Kearney then asked her to read
OL,7,Fthrough the messages and at this point
OL,8,Fthe clearly upset witness said "I
OL,9,Fdon't remember reading all of these
OL,10,Fand I don't really want to read these."
OL,12,FAfter the defence barrister continued
OL,13,Freferencing messages in the document,
OL,14,FMr Justice Kinney intervened and said:
OL,15,F"Mr Kearney, this witness has made it
OL,16,Fclear that she finds these messages
OL,17,Fdistressing."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773360185
OL,3,CWitness denies 'planning alibi,'
OL,4,CNatalie McNally murder trial told
OL,6,FShe was then asked if she was "sitting
OL,7,Fbeside him" when he was messaging Ms
OL,8,FMcNally that Sunday and she said: "I
OL,9,Fsaw him texting someone turned away
OL,10,Ffrom me and that's why I ended up
OL,11,Fgoing through his phone."
OL,13,FAt that point, the witness said "can
OL,14,Fwe not talking about these text
OL,15,Fmessages" then asked if she could set
OL,16,Fdown the document.
OL,18,FThe witness was also asked about a
OL,19,Fstatement she made to police on March
OL,20,F1 this year claiming her partner had
OL,21,Fbeen abusive during their relationship.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
